         <div type="translation">
            <p>Menophilos, son of Seleucos.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Both Menophilos and Seleucos are Greek names attested at Dura. The paleography (large and square hammer-cut letters) seems to suggests an earlier (possibly pre-Roman) date.</p>
            <p>Bibliography: Dura P.R. 2, p. 116; SEG 7:540; PH320781, https://inscriptions.packhum.org/text/320781?hs=18-31</p>
